
[1]construct

   CONSTRUCT, v.t. [L., to lay, dispose or set in order. See Structure.]

   1. To put together the parts of a thing in their proper place and
   order; to build; to form; as, to construct an edifice.

   2. To devise and compose, as to construct a new system; or simply to
   frame or form, as to construct a telescope. The word may include the
   invention, with the formation, or not, at the pleasure of the writer. A
   man constructs a ship according to a model; or a grammar by a new
   arrangement of principles; or a planetarium of a new form.

   3. To interpret or understand. [See Construe.]
